# Tests for lot error behaviour.

# ** 1. no lots available with --lots errors (exits 1)
<
2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50} @ $55
    assets:cash       $275
    revenues:gains

$ hledger -f- print --lots 2>/dev/null
>=1

# ** 2. Unclassified lotful commodity posting in asset account is a hard error with --lots.
# AAPL has lots: tag, assets:broker is an asset account, but the posting has no cost basis
# and no price, so classification fails. With --lots this is an error.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:

2026-01-15 mysterious
    assets:broker    10 AAPL
    income:mystery

$ hledger -f- bal assets --lots 2>&1
hledger: Error: -:4:
  | 2026-01-15 mysterious
4 |     assets:broker                                 10 AAPL
  |     income:mystery                               -10 AAPL

AAPL is declared lotful (commodity lots: tag) but this posting was not classified as
acquire, dispose, or transfer. Lot state will not be updated.
Possible fixes: add a cost basis ({$X}), a price (@ $X),
or check the account type declaration.
>=1

# ** 3. Zero-amount lotful posting (eg a balance assertion) is not an error with --lots.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:

2026-01-15 check balance
    assets:broker    0 AAPL = 0 AAPL
    income:mystery

$ hledger -f- bal assets --lots 2>&1
--------------------
                   0  
>=0

# ** 4. Implicit zero-amount lotful posting (balance assignment inferring zero) is not an error with --lots.
<
commodity AAPL  ; lots:

2026-01-15 check balance
    assets:broker    = 0 AAPL
    income:mystery

$ hledger -f- bal assets --lots 2>&1
--------------------
                   0  
>=0

# ** 5. Non-lotful commodity in asset account does not error with --lots.
<
2026-01-15 normal
    assets:checking    $100
    income:salary

$ hledger -f- bal assets --lots 2>&1
                $100  assets:checking
--------------------
                $100  
>=0

# ** 6. Gain posting does not trigger unclassified error with --lots.
<
account revenue:gains  ; type:V

2026-01-15 buy
    assets:stocks    10 AAPL {$50}
    assets:cash

2026-02-01 sell
    assets:stocks    -5 AAPL {$50} @ $60
    assets:cash      $300
    revenue:gains

$ hledger -f- bal assets --lots 2>&1
               $-200  assets:cash
              5 AAPL  assets:stocks:{2026-01-15, $50}
--------------------
               $-200
              5 AAPL  
>=0

# ** 7. Bare acquire with no inferable cost errors with --lots.
<
commodity T  ; lots:

2026-01-17 buy
    assets:wj       -52 A
    assets:broker    2220 T  ; @ $0.01
    equity:conversion

$ hledger -f- bal assets --lots 2>&1
hledger: Error: -:3:
3 | 2026-01-17 buy
  |     assets:wj                                    -52 A
  |     assets:broker                               2220 T  ; @ $0.01
  |     equity:conversion                             52 A
  |     equity:conversion                          -2220 T

T is lotful but this acquire posting has no cost basis or price.
No lot will be created.
>=1

# ** 8. A leaf account name enclosed in `{...}` that is not a valid lot name
# errors at load time with the parse-failure message.
<
2026-01-01 literal brace account
    assets:project:{not a lot}    $1
    equity:opening               $-1

$ hledger -f - print
>2 /cannot parse lot name part: not a lot/
>= 1

# ** 9. With --ignore-lots/-I, {...} leaf accounts are treated as ordinary subaccounts.
<
2026-01-01 literal brace account
    assets:project:{not a lot}    $1
    equity:opening               $-1

$ hledger -f- -I print
2026-01-01 literal brace account
    assets:project:{not a lot}                    $1
    equity:opening                               $-1

>=

# ** 10. `check lots` re-enables validation even when -I is used.
<
2026-01-01 literal brace account
    assets:project:{not a lot}    $1
    equity:opening               $-1

$ hledger -f- -I check lots
>2 /cannot parse lot name part: not a lot/
>= 1

# ** 11. A lot subaccount name missing required parts (date and cost) also
# triggers the lot-subaccount error.
<
2026-01-01 only label
    assets:project:{"label only"}    $1
    equity:opening                  $-1

$ hledger -f - print
>2 /lot subaccount name must contain a date and cost/
>= 1
